Hypothesis: a unexploded world war two bomb found on a street in sheffield has been declared safe.
Premise: It was the fourth time in a week a device - believed to be a World War Two munition - had been found in the city. The area was declared safe by South Yorkshire Police about four hours later. Three devices were uncovered in the same area last Wednesday and a temporary cordon was put in place.
